IONS:\n1. **Add complete `[workspace.package]` section**: Keep the `[workspace]` section but add all required fields to `[workspace.package]`:\n   - `version = \"0.1.0\"`\n   - `authors = [\"Linkerd Developers <cncf-linkerd-dev@lists.cncf.io>\"]` (or keep existing `authors` values)\n   - `license = \"Apache-2.0\"`\n   - `edition = \"2021\"`\n   - `publish = false`\n\n2. **Replace `{ workspace = true }` with actual values**: Remove `[workspace]` section AND replace all `{ workspace = true }` with actual values from root Cargo.toml.\n\n3. **Hybrid approach**: Add empty `[workspace]` table AND replace `{ workspace = true }` with actual values.\n\nRECOMMENDED APPROACH:\nOption 1 is best because:\n- It maintains the original intent (\"Prevent this from interfering with workspaces\")\n- It's a minimal change to the existing structure\n- We already have code to add `[workspace.package]` (just need to add all fields)\n\nHowever, we need to handle the `authors` field specially:\n- Some fuzz/Cargo.toml have `authors = [\"Automatically generated\"]`\n- Some have `authors = { workspace = true }`\n- We should preserve existing `authors` values when adding `[workspace.package]`\n\nIMPLEMENTATION PLAN:\nUpdate `fix_fuzz_cargo_toml` to:\n1. Check if `[workspace.package]` exists\n2. If not, add complete `[workspace.package]` section with all fields\n3. Use appropriate `authors` value (check existing value first)\n\nVALUES FROM ROOT CARGO.TOML:\n- `version = \"0.1.0\"`\n- `authors = [\"Linkerd Developers <cncf-linkerd-dev@lists.cncf.io>\"]`\n- `license = \"Apache-2.0\"`\n- `edition = \"2021\"`\n- `publish = false`\n\nLESSONS FROM ATTEMPT 3:\n- Removing `[workspace]` causes workspace membership confusion\n- Need to either make fuzz/Cargo.toml proper workspaces OR remove workspace inheritance\n- The original structure (workspace + inheritance) is fundamentally broken in Cargo"})
