  - STATE_UPDATE: {'generated_prompt': 'You are a premier expert in software testing. Fix the build for: linkerd2-proxy.\n\n--- 【EXPERT KNOWLEDGE & STRATEGIC GUIDANCE】 ---\nBased on the build log analysis, the Docker build failed with error: "failed to parse stage name \'gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:ba757e00046d6088d36985f18cee9198772b26c03b10c40364065888f6da04ba-rust\': invalid reference format". The issue is that Docker doesn\'t allow the "-rust" suffix after the SHA256 digest. The correct format should be "gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder-rust@sha256:ba757e00046d6088d36985f18cee9198772b26c03b10c40364065888f6da04ba". This is a Docker syntax error that needs to be fixed in the Dockerfile.\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 2] Good progress: Docker build now works with correct digest format. However, the fix was incomplete - only added \'edition\' to [workspace.package] but fuzz/Cargo.toml files also inherit \'version\', \'authors\', \'license\', and \'publish\'. Need to add all required fields to [workspace.package] section. The error moved from Docker syntax to Rust compilation, showing infrastructure is now working.\n- [Attempt 3] Removing [workspace] section caused Cargo to think fuzz packages want to be in parent workspace, but they\'re not in workspace.members. Need different approach: 1) Add empty [workspace] table (keeps them out of parent workspace but breaks inheritance), 2) Add complete [workspace.package] with all fields, or 3) Replace { workspace = true } with actual values. The error changed from missing workspace.package fields to workspace membership confusion.\n- [Attempt 1] The Dockerfile patch introduced an invalid image name format. Docker doesn\'t allow "-rust" suffix after SHA256 digest. The correct format should be "gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder-rust@sha256:digest". This is a simpler issue than the original Rust workspace configuration error.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2021 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:ba757e00046d6088d36985f18cee9198772b26c03b10c40364065888f6da04ba-rust\nRUN apt-get --yes update \\\n   && apt-get install --no-install-recommends --yes \\\n   libssl-dev \\\n   pkg-config \\\n   python \\\n   && apt-get clean \\\n   && rm --recursive --force /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\nRUN git clone  https://github.com/linkerd/linkerd2-proxy\n\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\nWORKDIR $SRC\n\nCOPY rustc.py $SRC/\n\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2021 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nif [ "$SANITIZER" = "coverage" ]\nthen\n  export RUSTFLAGS="$RUSTFLAGS -C debug-assertions=no"\n  chmod +x $SRC/rustc.py\n  export RUSTC="$SRC/rustc.py"\n  export CFLAGS=""\nfi\n\nBUILD_FUZZER="cargo fuzz build "\nTARGET_PATH="./fuzz/target/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/release"\nBASE="$SRC/linkerd2-proxy/linkerd"\n\ncd ${BASE}/app/inbound\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_inbound\n\ncd ${BASE}/addr/\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_addr\n\ncd ${BASE}/dns\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_dns\n\ncd ${BASE}/proxy/http\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_http\n\ncd ${BASE}/tls\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_tls\n\ncd ${BASE}/transport-header\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_raw $OUT/fuzz_transport_raw\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_structured $OUT/fuzz_transport_structured\n\necho "[libfuzzer]" > $OUT/fuzz_transport_raw.options\necho "detect_leaks=0" >> $OUT/fuzz_transport_raw.options\n\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nhomepage: "https://linkerd.io/"\nmain_repo: "https://github.com/linkerd/linkerd2-proxy"\nprimary_contact: "ver@buoyant.io"\nsanitizers:\n  - address\nfuzzing_engines:\n  - libfuzzer\nlanguage: rust\nauto_ccs:\n  - "eliza@buoyant.io"\n  - "kevinl@buoyant.io"\n  - "david@adalogics.com"\n\n### Content from: rustc.py ###\n#!/usr/bin/env python\n\n# Copyright 2021 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n\nimport sys\nimport subprocess\n\n#Disable coverage for troubling crates.\nsys.argv[0] = "rustc"\nif "tokio_util" in sys.argv or "hyper" in sys.argv:\n    try:\n        sys.argv.remove("-Zinstrument-coverage")\n    except:\n        pass\n    print(sys.argv)\nsubprocess.call(sys.argv)\n\n\n--- Project File Tree (Shallow View) ---\n📁 linkerd2-proxy\n├── 📄 CONTRIBUTING.md\n├── 📄 Cargo.lock\n├── 📄 Cargo.toml\n├── 📄 DCO\n├── 📄 Dockerfile\n├── 📄 GOVERNANCE.md\n├── 📄 LICENSE\n├── 📄 MAINTAINERS.md\n├── 📄 README.md\n├── 📄 deny.toml\n├── 📁 docs\n├── 📁 hyper-balance\n├── 📄 justfile\n├── 📁 linkerd\n├── 📁 linkerd2-proxy\n├── 📄 rust-toolchain.toml\n└── 📁 spiffe-proto\n\n--- Recent Commit Changes ---\n--- Commit Context Information ---\nProject Name: linkerd2-proxy\nError Report Time: 2024-11-6\nSelected Commit SHA: ac6f0006948a3b949b1ebbef6199135a4bf43fb5\n------------------------------\n\ncommit ac6f0006948a3b949b1ebbef6199135a4bf43fb5\nAuthor: Alejandro Pedraza <alejandro@buoyant.io>\nDate:   Wed Nov 6 11:16:24 2024 -0500\n\n    feat(inbound): Add HTTP local rate limiting support (#3305)\n    \n    Implemented inbound http local rate limiting, through the [governor crate](https://github.com/boinkor-net/governor), which uses the Generic Cell Rate algorithm.\n    \n    Ref linkerd/linkerd2#13231 for the policy-controller support.\n    ---------\n    \n    Co-authored-by: Oliver Gould <ver@buoyant.io>\n---\n Cargo.lock                                         |  54 +++++++\n linkerd/app/core/src/errors/respond.rs             |  10 ++\n linkerd/app/gateway/src/http/tests.rs              |   1 +\n linkerd/app/inbound/Cargo.toml                     |   3 +\n linkerd/app/inbound/src/accept.rs                  |   1 +\n linkerd/app/inbound/src/detect/tests.rs            |   1 +\n linkerd/app/inbound/src/http/server.rs             |   4 +\n linkerd/app/inbound/src/http/tests.rs              |   1 +\n linkerd/app/inbound/src/policy.rs                  |   3 +-\n linkerd/app/inbound/src/policy/defaults.rs         |   1 +\n linkerd/app/inbound/src/policy/http.rs             |  19 ++-\n link