  - STATE_UPDATE: {'generated_prompt': 'You are a premier expert in software testing. Fix the build for: linkerd2-proxy.\n\n--- 【EXPERT KNOWLEDGE & STRATEGIC GUIDANCE】 ---\nBased on the build log analysis, the current error is: "Cannot use local checkout with \'WORKDIR: /src\'". This is a Docker/OSS-Fuzz configuration error that occurred when trying to use "source" build mode (mounting local source code) with a Dockerfile that has WORKDIR $SRC and clones the repository inside the container. The Dockerfile is designed to clone the repository itself, but when using local checkout mode, OSS-Fuzz expects the source code to be mounted at /src, causing a conflict. Need to either use "standard" build mode (let Dockerfile clone the repo) or modify the Dockerfile to work with mounted source code. The original Rust workspace inheritance error in fuzz/Cargo.toml files was addressed in a previous attempt but caused complexity overload and regression.\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 1] The Dockerfile patch introduced an invalid image name format. Docker doesn\'t allow "-rust" suffix after SHA256 digest. The correct format should be "gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder-rust@sha256:digest". This is a simpler issue than the original Rust workspace configuration error.\n- [Attempt 2] Good progress: Docker build now works with correct digest format. However, the fix was incomplete - only added \'edition\' to [workspace.package] but fuzz/Cargo.toml files also inherit \'version\', \'authors\', \'license\', and \'publish\'. Need to add all required fields to [workspace.package] section. The error moved from Docker syntax to Rust compilation, showing infrastructure is now working.\n- [Attempt 3] Removing [workspace] section caused Cargo to think fuzz packages want to be in parent workspace, but they\'re not in workspace.members. Need different approach: 1) Add empty [workspace] table (keeps them out of parent workspace but breaks inheritance), 2) Add complete [workspace.package] with all fields, or 3) Replace { workspace = true } with actual values. The error changed from missing workspace.package fields to workspace membership confusion.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2021 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder-rust@sha256:ba757e00046d6088d36985f18cee9198772b26c03b10c40364065888f6da04ba\nRUN apt-get --yes update \\\n   && apt-get install --no-install-recommends --yes \\\n   libssl-dev \\\n   pkg-config \\\n   python \\\n   && apt-get clean \\\n   && rm --recursive --force /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\nRUN git clone  https://github.com/linkerd/linkerd2-proxy $SRC/linkerd2-proxy\n\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\nWORKDIR $SRC\n\nCOPY rustc.py $SRC/\n\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2021 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nif [ "$SANITIZER" = "coverage" ]\nthen\n  export RUSTFLAGS="$RUSTFLAGS -C debug-assertions=no"\n  chmod +x $SRC/rustc.py\n  export RUSTC="$SRC/rustc.py"\n  export CFLAGS=""\nfi\n\n# Function to fix fuzz/Cargo.toml files by removing the [workspace] section\n# This allows them to properly inherit from the parent workspace\nfix_fuzz_cargo_toml() {\n  local fuzz_dir="$1"\n  local cargo_toml="${fuzz_dir}/fuzz/Cargo.toml"\n  \n  if [ -f "$cargo_toml" ]; then\n    echo "Fixing $cargo_toml"\n    # Check if [workspace] section exists\n    if grep -q "^\\[workspace\\]" "$cargo_toml"; then\n      # Remove the [workspace] section and its contents (3 lines total)\n      # This includes: [workspace], members = ["."], and resolver = "2"\n      sed -i \'/^\\[workspace\\]/,+2d\' "$cargo_toml"\n    fi\n  fi\n}\n\nBUILD_FUZZER="cargo fuzz build "\nTARGET_PATH="./fuzz/target/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/release"\nBASE="$SRC/linkerd2-proxy/linkerd"\n\n# Fix and build each fuzz target\ncd ${BASE}/app/inbound\nfix_fuzz_cargo_toml "."\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_inbound\n\ncd ${BASE}/addr/\nfix_fuzz_cargo_toml "."\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_addr\n\ncd ${BASE}/dns\nfix_fuzz_cargo_toml "."\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_dns\n\ncd ${BASE}/proxy/http\nfix_fuzz_cargo_toml "."\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_http\n\ncd ${BASE}/tls\nfix_fuzz_cargo_toml "."\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_1 $OUT/fuzz_tls\n\ncd ${BASE}/transport-header\nfix_fuzz_cargo_toml "."\n${BUILD_FUZZER}\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_raw $OUT/fuzz_transport_raw\ncp ${TARGET_PATH}/fuzz_target_structured $OUT/fuzz_transport_structured\n\necho "[libfuzzer]" > $OUT/fuzz_transport_raw.options\necho "detect_leaks=0" >> $OUT/fuzz_transport_raw.options\n\n\n